invalid_snapshot_analysis.conclusion: ALL better N values have overlaps - improvements come FROM the overlaps

repair_attempt.conclusion: Moving trees apart to remove overlaps expands bounding box, losing all improvement

gradient_descent.conclusion: Baseline is at local optimum - gradient is zero in all directions

overall_conclusion: The baseline is at an EXTREMELY STRONG LOCAL OPTIMUM. Invalid snapshots achieve better scores BECAUSE of overlaps, not despite them. The trees are packed too tightly to be valid.
